rosario@theory.lcs.mit.edu (Rosario Gennaro) writes:

>lately I have been interested in the condtional access problem 
>for encrypted broadcasted signal (like for example Pay-TV). 

A few first pointers in the literature are in ftp.uni-erlangen.de
pub/Multimedia/VideoCrypt/Videocrypt-References and other files there.
In addition, there is a software (season13.zip) that allows a PC to
emulate the card of a popular European pay-tv access control system.
Before the most recent card exchange of a British station, this software
was actually used by a few enthusiasts in order to descramble pay-tv
without a subscription. This software contains the crypto algorithm and
the secret key of the old cards. The new cards contain a new algorithm/key.

Markus

